#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="mn144"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "mn144:0.1"
msgid "Majjhima Nikāya 144 "
msgstr "Middle Discourses 144 "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "mn144:0.2"
msgid "Channovādasutta "
msgstr "Advice to Channa "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p><span class="evam">
#. REF: nya1, sc1
msgctxt "mn144:1.1"
msgid "Evaṃ me sutaṃ—"
msgstr "So I have heard. "

#. HTML: </span>
msgctxt "mn144:1.2"
msgid "ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā rājagahe viharati veḷuvane kalandakanivāpe. "
msgstr "At one time the Buddha was staying near Rājagaha, in the Bamboo Grove, the squirrels’ feeding ground. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya2
msgctxt "mn144:2.1"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena āyasmā ca sāriputto āyasmā ca mahācundo āyasmā ca channo gijjhakūṭe pabbate viharanti. "
msgstr "Now at that time the venerables Sāriputta, Mahācunda, and Channa were staying on the Vulture’s Peak Mountain. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya3
msgctxt "mn144:3.1"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena āyasmā channo ābādhiko hoti dukkhito bāḷhagilāno. "
msgstr "Now at that time Venerable Channa was sick, suffering, gravely ill. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn144:3.2"
msgid "Atha kho āyasmā sāriputto sāyanhasamayaṃ paṭisallānā vuṭṭhito yenāyasmā mahācundo tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā āyasmantaṃ mahācundaṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr "Then in the late afternoon, Venerable Sāriputta came out of retreat, went to Venerable Mahācunda and said to him, "

msgctxt "mn144:3.3"
msgid "“āyāmāvuso cunda, yenāyasmā channo tenupasaṅkamissāma gilānapucchakā”ti. "
msgstr "“Come, Reverend Cunda, let’s go to see Venerable Channa and ask about his illness.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn144:3.4"
msgid "“Evamāvuso”ti kho āyasmā mahācundo āyasmato sāriputtassa paccassosi. "
msgstr "“Yes, reverend,” replied Mahācunda. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya4, pts-vp-pli3.264, sc2
msgctxt "mn144:4.1"
msgid "Atha kho āyasmā ca sāriputto āyasmā ca mahācundo yenāyasmā channo tenupasaṅkamiṃsu; upasaṅkamitvā āyasmatā channena saddhiṃ sammodiṃsu. "
msgstr "And then Sāriputta and Mahācunda went to see Channa and exchanged greetings with him. "

msgctxt "mn144:4.2"
msgid "Sammodanīyaṃ kathaṃ sāraṇīyaṃ vītisāretvā ekamantaṃ nisīdiṃsu. Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho āyasmā sāriputto āyasmantaṃ channaṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr "When the greetings and polite conversation were over, they sat down to one side. Then Sāriputta said to Channa, "

msgctxt "mn144:4.3"
msgid "“kacci te, āvuso channa, khamanīyaṃ, kacci yāpanīyaṃ? Kacci te dukkhā vedanā paṭikkamanti, no abhikkamanti; paṭikkamosānaṃ paññāyati, no abhikkamo”ti? "
msgstr "“I hope you’re keeping well, Reverend Channa; I hope you’re alright. I hope that your pain is fading, not growing, that its fading is evident, not its growing.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya5, sc3
msgctxt "mn144:5.1"
msgid "“Na me, āvuso sāriputta, khamanīyaṃ na yāpanīyaṃ. Bāḷhā me dukkhā vedanā abhikkamanti, no paṭikkamanti; abhikkamosānaṃ paññāyati, no paṭikkamo. "
msgstr "“Reverend Sāriputta, I’m not keeping well, I’m not alright. The pain is terrible and growing, not fading; its growing is evident, not its fading. "

msgctxt "mn144:5.2"
msgid "Seyyathāpi, āvuso sāriputta, balavā puriso tiṇhena sikharena muddhani abhimattheyya; evameva kho me, āvuso sāriputta, adhimattā vātā muddhani ūhananti. "
msgstr "The winds piercing my head are so severe, it feels like a strong man drilling into my head with a sharp point. "

msgctxt "mn144:5.3"
msgid "Na me, āvuso sāriputta, khamanīyaṃ na yāpanīyaṃ. Bāḷhā me dukkhā vedanā abhikkamanti, no paṭikkamanti; abhikkamosānaṃ paññāyati no paṭikkamo. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "mn144:5.4"
msgid "Seyyathāpi, āvuso sāriputta, balavā puriso daḷhena varattakkhaṇḍena sīse sīsaveṭhaṃ dadeyya; evameva kho me, āvuso sāriputta, adhimattā sīse sīsavedanā. "
msgstr "The pain in my head is so severe, it feels like a strong man tightening a tough leather strap around my head. "

msgctxt "mn144:5.5"
msgid "Na me, āvuso sāriputta, khamanīyaṃ na yāpanīyaṃ. Bāḷhā me dukkhā vedanā abhikkamanti, no paṭikkamanti; abhikkamosānaṃ paññāyati, no paṭikkamo. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "mn144:5.6"
msgid "Seyyathāpi, āvuso sāriputta, dakkho goghātako vā goghātakantevāsī vā tiṇhena govikantanena kucchiṃ parikanteyya; evameva kho me, āvuso sāriputta, adhimattā vātā kucchiṃ parikantanti. "
msgstr "The winds piercing my belly are so severe, it feels like a deft butcher or their apprentice is slicing my belly open with a meat cleaver. "

msgctxt "mn144:5.7"
msgid "Na me, āvuso sāriputta, khamanīyaṃ na yāpanīyaṃ. Bāḷhā me dukkhā vedanā abhikkamanti, no paṭikkamanti; abhikkamosānaṃ paññāyati, no paṭikkamo. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "mn144:5.8"
msgid "Seyyathāpi, āvuso sāriputta, dve balavanto purisā dubbalataraṃ purisaṃ nānābāhāsu gahetvā aṅgārakāsuyā santāpeyyuṃ samparitāpeyyuṃ; evameva kho me, āvuso sāriputta, adhimatto kāyasmiṃ ḍāho. "
msgstr "The burning in my body is so severe, it feels like two strong men grabbing a weaker man by the arms to burn and scorch him on a pit of glowing coals. "

msgctxt "mn144:5.9"
msgid "Na me, āvuso sāriputta, khamanīyaṃ na yāpanīyaṃ. Bāḷhā me dukkhā vedanā abhikkamanti, no paṭikkamanti; abhikkamosānaṃ paññāyati, no paṭikkamo. "
msgstr "I’m not keeping well, I’m not alright. The pain is terrible and growing, not fading; its growing is evident, not its fading. "

msgctxt "mn144:5.10"
msgid "Satthaṃ, āvuso sāriputta, āharissāmi, nāvakaṅkhāmi jīvitan”ti. "
msgstr "Reverend Sāriputta, I will slit my wrists. I don’t wish to live.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya6, sc4
msgctxt "mn144:6.1"
msgid "“Māyasmā channo satthaṃ āharesi. "
msgstr "“Please don’t slit your wrists! "

msgctxt "mn144:6.2"
msgid "Yāpetāyasmā channo. Yāpentaṃ mayaṃ āyasmantaṃ channaṃ icchāma. "
msgstr "Venerable Channa, keep going! We want you to keep going. "

msgctxt "mn144:6.3"
msgid "Sace āyasmato channassa natthi sappāyāni bhojanāni, ahaṃ āyasmato channassa sappāyāni bhojanāni pariyesissāmi. "
msgstr "If you don’t have any suitable food, we’ll find it for you. "

msgctxt "mn144:6.4"
msgid "Sace āyasmato channassa natthi sappāyāni bhesajjāni, ahaṃ āyasmato channassa sappāyāni bhesajjāni pariyesissāmi. "
msgstr "If you don’t have suitable medicine, we’ll find it for you. "

msgctxt "mn144:6.5"
msgid "Sace āyasmato channassa natthi patirūpā upaṭṭhākā, ahaṃ āyasmantaṃ channaṃ upaṭṭhahissāmi. "
msgstr "If you don’t have a capable carer, we’ll find one for you. "

msgctxt "mn144:6.6"
msgid "Māyasmā channo satthaṃ āharesi. "
msgstr "Please don’t slit your wrists! "

msgctxt "mn144:6.7"
msgid "Yāpetāyasmā channo. Yāpentaṃ mayaṃ āyasmantaṃ channaṃ icchāmā”ti. "
msgstr "Venerable Channa, keep going! We want you to keep going.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya7, sc5
msgctxt "mn144:7.1"
msgid "“Napi me, āvuso sāriputta, natthi sappāyāni bhojanāni; "
msgstr "“Reverend Sāriputta, it’s not that I don’t have suitable food, "

msgctxt "mn144:7.2"
msgid "napi me natthi sappāyāni bhesajjāni; "
msgstr "or suitable medicine, "

msgctxt "mn144:7.3"
msgid "napi me natthi patirūpā upaṭṭhākā; "
msgstr "or a capable carer. "

msgctxt "mn144:7.4"
msgid "api cāvuso sāriputta, pariciṇṇo me satthā dīgharattaṃ manāpeneva no amanāpena. "
msgstr "Moreover, for a long time now I have served the Teacher with love, not without love. "

msgctxt "mn144:7.5"
msgid "Etañhi, āvuso sāriputta, sāvakassa patirūpaṃ yaṃ satthāraṃ paricareyya manāpeneva no amanāpena. "
msgstr "For it is proper for a disciple to serve the Teacher with love, not without love. "

#. VAR: evametaṃ → evameva kho tvaṃ (mr)
msgctxt "mn144:7.6"
msgid "‘Anupavajjaṃ channo bhikkhu satthaṃ āharissatī’ti evametaṃ, āvuso sāriputta, dhārehī”ti. "
msgstr "You should remember this: ‘The mendicant Channa slit his wrists blamelessly.’” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya8
msgctxt "mn144:8.1"
msgid "“Puccheyyāma mayaṃ āyasmantaṃ channaṃ kañcideva desaṃ, sace āyasmā channo okāsaṃ karoti pañhassa veyyākaraṇāyā”ti. "
msgstr "“I’d like to ask you about a certain point, if you’d take the time to answer.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn144:8.2"
msgid "“Pucchāvuso sāriputta, sutvā vedissāmī”ti. "
msgstr "“Ask, Reverend Sāriputta. When I’ve heard it I’ll know.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya9, pts-vp-pli3.265, sc6
msgctxt "mn144:9.1"
msgid "“Cakkhuṃ, āvuso channa, cakkhuviññāṇaṃ cakkhuviññāṇaviññātabbe dhamme ‘etaṃ mama, esohamasmi, eso me attā’ti samanupassasi? "
msgstr "“Reverend Channa, do you regard the eye, eye consciousness, and things knowable by eye consciousness in this way: ‘This is mine, I am this, this is my self’? "

msgctxt "mn144:9.2"
msgid "Sotaṃ, āvuso channa, sotaviññāṇaṃ … pe … "
msgstr "Do you regard the ear … "

msgctxt "mn144:9.3"
msgid "ghānaṃ, āvuso channa, ghānaviññāṇaṃ … "
msgstr "nose … "

msgctxt "mn144:9.4"
msgid "jivhaṃ, āvuso channa, jivhāviññāṇaṃ … "
msgstr "tongue … "

msgctxt "mn144:9.5"
msgid "kāyaṃ, āvuso channa, kāyaviññāṇaṃ … "
msgstr "body … "

msgctxt "mn144:9.6"
msgid "manaṃ, āvuso channa, manoviññāṇaṃ manoviññāṇaviññātabbe dhamme ‘etaṃ mama, esohamasmi, eso me attā’ti samanupassasī”ti? "
msgstr "mind, mind consciousness, and things knowable by mind consciousness in this way: ‘This is mine, I am this, this is my self’?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc7
msgctxt "mn144:9.7"
msgid "“Cakkhuṃ, āvuso sāriputta, cakkhuviññāṇaṃ cakkhuviññāṇaviññātabbe dhamme ‘netaṃ mama, nesohamasmi, na meso attā’ti samanupassāmi. "
msgstr "“Reverend Sāriputta, I regard the eye, eye consciousness, and things knowable by eye consciousness in this way: ‘This is not mine, I am not this, this is not my self.’ "

msgctxt "mn144:9.8"
msgid "Sotaṃ, āvuso sāriputta … pe … "
msgstr "I regard the ear … "

msgctxt "mn144:9.9"
msgid "ghānaṃ, āvuso sāriputta … "
msgstr "nose … "

msgctxt "mn144:9.10"
msgid "jivhaṃ, āvuso sāriputta … "
msgstr "tongue … "

msgctxt "mn144:9.11"
msgid "kāyaṃ, āvuso sāriputta … "
msgstr "body … "

msgctxt "mn144:9.12"
msgid "manaṃ, āvuso sāriputta, manoviññāṇaṃ manoviññāṇaviññātabbe dhamme ‘netaṃ mama, nesohamasmi, na meso attā’ti samanupassāmī”ti. "
msgstr "mind, mind consciousness, and things knowable by mind consciousness in this way: ‘This is not mine, I am not this, this is not my self’.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya10, sc8
msgctxt "mn144:10.1"
msgid "“Cakkhusmiṃ, āvuso channa, cakkhuviññāṇe cakkhuviññāṇaviññātabbesu dhammesu kiṃ disvā kiṃ abhiññāya cakkhuṃ cakkhuviññāṇaṃ cakkhuviññāṇaviññātabbe dhamme ‘netaṃ mama, nesohamasmi, na meso attā’ti samanupassasi? "
msgstr "“Reverend Channa, what have you seen, what have you directly known in these things that you regard them in this way: ‘This is not mine, I am not this, this is not my self’?” "

msgctxt "mn144:10.2"
msgid "Sotasmiṃ, āvuso channa, sotaviññāṇe … "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "mn144:10.3"
msgid "ghānasmiṃ, āvuso channa, ghānaviññāṇe … "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "mn144:10.4"
msgid "jivhāya, āvuso channa, jivhāviññāṇe … "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "mn144:10.5"
msgid "kāyasmiṃ, āvuso channa, kāyaviññāṇe … "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "mn144:10.6"
msgid "manasmiṃ, āvuso channa, manoviññāṇe manoviññāṇaviññātabbesu dhammesu kiṃ disvā kiṃ abhiññāya manaṃ manoviññāṇaṃ manoviññāṇaviññātabbe dhamme ‘netaṃ mama, nesohamasmi, na meso attā’ti samanupassasī”ti? "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli3.266, sc9
msgctxt "mn144:10.7"
msgid "“Cakkhusmiṃ, āvuso sāriputta, cakkhuviññāṇe cakkhuviññāṇaviññātabbesu dhammesu nirodhaṃ disvā nirodhaṃ abhiññāya cakkhuṃ cakkhuviññāṇaṃ cakkhuviññāṇaviññātabbe dhamme ‘netaṃ mama, nesohamasmi, na meso attā’ti samanupassāmi. "
msgstr "“Reverend Sāriputta, after seeing cessation, after directly knowing cessation in these things I regard them in this way: ‘This is not mine, I am not this, this is not my self’.” "

msgctxt "mn144:10.8"
msgid "Sotasmiṃ, āvuso sāriputta, sotaviññāṇe … "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "mn144:10.9"
msgid "ghānasmiṃ, āvuso sāriputta, ghānaviññāṇe … "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "mn144:10.10"
msgid "jivhāya, āvuso sāriputta, jivhāviññāṇe … "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "mn144:10.11"
msgid "kāyasmiṃ, āvuso sāriputta, kāyaviññāṇe … "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "mn144:10.12"
msgid "manasmiṃ, āvuso sāriputta, manoviññāṇe manoviññāṇaviññātabbesu dhammesu nirodhaṃ disvā nirodhaṃ abhiññāya manaṃ manoviññāṇaṃ manoviññāṇaviññātabbe dhamme ‘netaṃ mama, nesohamasmi, na meso attā’ti samanupassāmī”ti. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya11, sc10
msgctxt "mn144:11.1"
msgid "Evaṃ vutte, āyasmā mahācundo āyasmantaṃ channaṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr "When he said this, Venerable Mahācunda said to Venerable Channa: "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn144:11.2"
msgid "“tasmātiha, āvuso channa, idampi tassa bhagavato sāsanaṃ, niccakappaṃ manasi kātabbaṃ: "
msgstr "“So, Reverend Channa, you should pay close attention to this instruction of the Buddha whenever you can: "

msgctxt "mn144:11.3"
msgid "‘nissitassa calitaṃ, anissitassa calitaṃ natthi. "
msgstr "‘For the dependent there is agitation. For the independent there’s no agitation. "

msgctxt "mn144:11.4"
msgid "Calite asati passaddhi, "
msgstr "When there’s no agitation there is tranquility. "

msgctxt "mn144:11.5"
msgid "passaddhiyā sati nati na hoti. "
msgstr "When there is tranquility there’s no inclination. "

msgctxt "mn144:11.6"
msgid "Natiyā asati āgatigati na hoti. "
msgstr "When there’s no inclination there’s no coming and going. "

msgctxt "mn144:11.7"
msgid "Āgatigatiyā asati cutūpapāto na hoti. "
msgstr "When there’s no coming and going there’s no passing away and reappearing. "

msgctxt "mn144:11.8"
msgid "Cutūpapāte asati nevidha na huraṃ na ubhayamantarena. "
msgstr "When there’s no passing away and reappearing there’s no this world or world beyond or between the two. "

msgctxt "mn144:11.9"
msgid "Esevanto dukkhassā’”ti. "
msgstr "Just this is the end of suffering.’” "

msgctxt "mn144:11.10"
msgid "Atha kho āyasmā ca sāriputto āyasmā ca mahācundo āyasmantaṃ channaṃ iminā ovādena ovaditvā uṭṭhāyāsanā pakkamiṃsu. "
msgstr "And when the venerables Sāriputta and Mahācunda had given Venerable Channa this advice they got up from their seat and left. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya12, sc11
msgctxt "mn144:12.1"
msgid "Atha kho āyasmā channo acirapakkante āyasmante ca sāriputte āyasmante ca mahācunde satthaṃ āharesi. "
msgstr "Not long after those venerables had left, Venerable Channa slit his wrists. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya13
msgctxt "mn144:13.1"
msgid "Atha kho āyasmā sāriputto yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho āyasmā sāriputto bhagavantaṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr "Then Sāriputta went up to the Buddha, bowed, sat down to one side, and said to him, "

msgctxt "mn144:13.2"
msgid "“āyasmatā, bhante, channena satthaṃ āharitaṃ. "
msgstr "“Sir, Venerable Channa has slit his wrists. "

msgctxt "mn144:13.3"
msgid "Tassa kā gati, ko abhisamparāyo”ti? "
msgstr "Where has he been reborn in his next life?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn144:13.4"
msgid "“Nanu te, sāriputta, channena bhikkhunā sammukhāyeva anupavajjatā byākatā”ti? "
msgstr "“Sāriputta, didn’t the mendicant Channa declare his blamelessness to you personally?” "

# NOTE: the variant spellings between MN and SN seem irreconcilable. I follow BB in CDB, which is also accepted by Malalasekera in DPPN.
#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn144:13.5"
msgid "“Atthi, bhante, pubbajiraṃ nāma vajjigāmo. "
msgstr "“Sir, there is a Vajjian village named Pubbavijjhana "

msgctxt "mn144:13.6"
msgid "Tatthāyasmato channassa mittakulāni suhajjakulāni upavajjakulānī”ti. "
msgstr "where Channa had families with whom he was friendly, intimate, and familiar.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. VAR: Honti → posanti (mr)
msgctxt "mn144:13.7"
msgid "“Honti hete, sāriputta, channassa bhikkhuno mittakulāni suhajjakulāni upavajjakulāni. "
msgstr "“The mendicant Channa did indeed have such families. "

msgctxt "mn144:13.8"
msgid "Nāhaṃ, sāriputta, ettāvatā ‘saupavajjo’ti vadāmi. "
msgstr "But this is not enough for me to call someone ‘blameworthy’. "

msgctxt "mn144:13.9"
msgid "Yo kho, sāriputta, imañca kāyaṃ nikkhipati aññañca kāyaṃ upādiyati tamahaṃ ‘saupavajjo’ti vadāmi. "
msgstr "When someone lays down this body and takes up another body, I call them ‘blameworthy’. "

msgctxt "mn144:13.10"
msgid "Taṃ channassa bhikkhuno natthi. "
msgstr "But the mendicant Channa did no such thing. "

msgctxt "mn144:13.11"
msgid "‘Anupavajjo channo bhikkhu satthaṃ āharesī’ti evametaṃ, sāriputta, dhārehī”ti. "
msgstr "You should remember this: ‘The mendicant Channa slit his wrists blamelessly.’” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc12
msgctxt "mn144:13.12"
msgid "Idamavoca bhagavā. "
msgstr "That is what the Buddha said. "

msgctxt "mn144:13.13"
msgid "Attamano āyasmā sāriputto bhagavato bhāsitaṃ abhinandīti. "
msgstr "Satisfied, Venerable Sāriputta was happy with what the Buddha said. "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "mn144:13.14"
msgid "Channovādasuttaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ dutiyaṃ. "
msgstr ""

